curity arrangements. Public Security in Federal Polities identifies differences and similarities, highlights best practices, and draws out lessons for both particular federations, and for federal systems in general. This book is essential reading for scholars, students, practitioners as well as policy- and decision-makers of security and federalism.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 0aFederal governmentvCase studies. 0aGlobalizationvCase studies. 0aNational securityvCase studies. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Comparative Politics.2bisacsh  acomparative federalism.  afederalism.  aglobalization.  ainstitutional design.  apublic administration.  apublic policy.  apublic.  asecurity studies.  asecurity.1 aHataley, Todd, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHataley, Tom, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKenkel, Kai Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKilroy Jr, Richard J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKölling, Mario, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKölling, Mario, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLeuprecht, Christian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLeuprecht, Christian, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMehra, Ajay K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMohar, Edgar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMohler, Markus H. F., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMuntingh, Lukas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchweizer, Rainer J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSteytler, Nico,